org.jorlib.frameworks.columnGeneration.branchAndPrice

Class AbstractBranchCreator<T,U extends AbstractColumn<T,V>,V extends AbstractPricingProblem<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jorlib.frameworks.columnGeneration.branchAndPrice.AbstractBranchCreator<T,U,V>

  • public abstract class AbstractBranchCreator<T,U extends AbstractColumn<T,V>,V extends AbstractPricingProblem<T>>
extends Object
    Given a fractional solution obtained after solving a node in the Branch-and-Price tree, this class creates a number of branches, thereby spawning 2 or more child nodes.
    Version:
    5-5-2015
    Author:
    Joris Kinable

      • branch

        public List<BAPNode<T,U>> branch(BAPNode<T,U> parentNode)
        Main method of this class which performs the branching. The method first invokes canPerformBranching to check whether branches can be created. If the latter returns true, the method createBranch(BAPNode, BranchingDecision, List, List) is invoked.
        Parameters:
        parentNode - Node on which we branch
        Returns:
        List of child nodes if branches could be created, and empty list otherwise

      • canPerformBranching

        protected abstract boolean canPerformBranching(List<U> solution)
        This method decides whether the branching can be performed. To reduce overhead, this method should also store on which aspect of the problem it should branch, e.g. an edge or a variable.
        Parameters:
        solution - Fractional column generation solution
        Returns:
        Returns true if the branching can be performed, false otherwise
